<subSubSection lastPageId="102" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="102" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
This species was reported for Jammu &amp; Kashmir and Himachal Pradesh, India (
<bibRefCitation author="Dhar, U" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" refId="B20" refString="Dhar, U, Kachroo, P, 1983. Alpine flora of Kashmir Himalaya. Scientific Publishers, Jodhpur." title="Alpine flora of Kashmir Himalaya. Scientific Publishers, Jodhpur." year="1983">Dhar and Kachroo 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chowdhery, HJ" editor="Chowdhery, HJ" journalOrPublisher="2. Botanical Survey of India, New Delhi" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" pagination="601 - 606" refId="B14" refString="Chowdhery, HJ, 1984. Chenopodiaceae. In: Chowdhery, HJ, Wadhwa, BM, Eds., Flora of Himachal Pradesh, Vol. 2. Botanical Survey of India, New Delhi: 601 - 606" title="Chenopodiaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Himachal Pradesh, Vol." year="1984">Chowdhery 1984</bibRefCitation>
), but all examined specimens belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. J. Scott, Fedd. Repert. 89 (2 - 3): 108" authorityYear="1978" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Hydrozoa" family="Chenopodiacea" genus="Bassia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bassia scoparia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="scoparia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
<pageBreakToken pageId="102" pageNumber="103" start="start">Bassia</pageBreakToken>
scoparia
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="All., Melanges Philos. Math. Soc. Roy. Turin 3: 177" authorityYear="1766" class="Hydrozoa" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Bassia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
. However, the presence of 
<taxonomicName family="Chenopodiacea" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. indica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">B. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is possible in the foothills of North Himalaya (0-1500 m a.s.l.), as it is known from neighbouring areas, e.g. state of Haryana, India (BSD! LE!) and Punjab Province, Pakistan (K!).
</paragraph>
